Kari‚Äôs Law ‚Äî my bipartisan bill with @SenatorFischer ‚Äî was signed into law yesterday. It makes sure that hotels, offices and other buildings let people direct-dial 9-1-1 in an emergency. This law helps ensure that no family‚Äôs calls for help go unanswered.

A federal grand jury just indicted 13 Russians for interfering in the 2016 elections‚Äîlargely through social media engineering & anonymous online ads. My #HonestAds Act w/ @SenJohnMcCain & @MarkWarner would make public who bought an online political ad‚Äîthe same rule as TV ads.

The killer in the Parkland, Florida school massacre should never have been allowed to purchase an AR-15.  I have long advocated for sensible gun legislation, including a bipartisan background check bill. It is time to bring these bills up for a vote. They will save lives.

Parents should be able to drop their kids off at the start of the day and expect that they will come home safe. My heart goes out to the Parkland, FL community & all the students, teachers, faculty, & families connected with Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School.

Joined my colleagues to call for immediate action to protect our dreamers ‚Äî 97% of whom are working and/or still in school. We *must* get this done and help these young men and women who only know America as their home.

Admin wants to completely cut the LIHEAP program ‚Äî which provides heating assistance for thousands of Minnesotans ‚Äî in its next budget. That‚Äôs unacceptable. Could get to -6¬∫ in Brainerd this week! LIHEAP is vital to many in MN who need it to heat their homes in tough winters.

More on Nolan(despite 5am vote he‚Äôs still talking to everyone on plane): When Rick speaks he‚Äôs always honest. When he takes on a fight he never backs down. W/a twinkle in his eye & a big heart, he‚Äôs been a joy to work w/...&by the way, he‚Äôs such a rabble rouser, he‚Äôs not done yet

Just met with Dreamers from MN and the Catholic Conference. The deadline is upon us.  The Republican congress can‚Äôt allow 800,000 kids to be deported.  Pass the Dream Act now.
Great game both teams. Congratulations Eagles.  And I‚Äôm proud of our state for being a wonderful Super Bowl host!

If the President is truly serious about doing more to bring down the cost of Rx drugs, we could start by passing my bipartisan bills to lower costs for Americans everywhere & allow Medicare Part D negotiation! He should tell his party to allow for up or down votes on these bills.

Tonight my guest for the State of the Union is Shelly Elkington, whose daughter died after battling an opioid addiction. We must do more to fight the opioid epidemic, getting people treatment & stopping these drugs from coming into the US.
